Macro and micro chemistry- comparison of fruits

Between-species analysis of macronutrients (protein; sugar) and volatile chemicals.

library(nlme)

xdata <- read.csv("data.csv", header = TRUE)
xtree <- read.nexus("phylogeny.nex")

Distributions

hist(xdata$perc.NS) #skewed

hist(xdata$perc.terpenoids)#acceptable

hist(xdata$perc.MEST) #highly skewed

hist(xdata$perc.sugar) #acceptable

Transformations?

hist(xdata$perc.NS) #zero inflated

hist(log(xdata$perc.terpenoids))#much worse

hist(sqrt(xdata$perc.MEST))#bad

hist(log(xdata$perc.MEST+0.00001))#not helpful - use binary

hist(log(xdata$perc.sugar)) #acceptable

hist(log(xdata$perc.nitrogen))#good

TRANSFORMATIONS

binary.ns <- xdata$perc.NS ##Convert percentage NS to binary variable
binary.ns[binary.ns > 0] <- 1

binary.mest <- xdata$perc.MEST ##Convert percentage methyl/ethyl esters to binary variable
binary.mest[binary.mest > 0] <-1

log.perc.sugar <- log(xdata$perc.sugar) #log transform perc sugar 
log.perc.nitrogen <- log(xdata$perc.nitrogen) #log transform perc nitrogen

xdata <- cbind(xdata, binary.ns, log.perc.nitrogen, log.perc.sugar, binary.mest)

rownames(xdata) <- xdata$species

SUGAR - terpenoids and methyl/ethyl esters

sub.data <- subset(xdata, xdata$species != "Chassalia_ternifolia") #remove sepcies with no data
sub.tree <- drop.tip(xtree, "Chassalia_ternifolia")

m.sugar <- gls(log.perc.sugar ~ perc.terpenoids + binary.mest, data = sub.data, correlation = corBrownian(phy = sub.tree), method = "ML")

m.sugar.null <- gls(log.perc.sugar ~ 1, data = sub.data, correlation = corBrownian(phy = sub.tree), method = "ML") #null model

summary(m.sugar)

## regression coefficients

text("pgls: p = 0.016", x = 60, y = 2.60, cex = 1.5, srt = -13)
text("A", x = 0, y = 1.2, cex = 2)

binary.label <- rep("No Me/Et esters in scent", nrow(sub.data))
binary.label[sub.data$binary.mest == 1] <- "Me/Et esters in scent"

boxplot(sub.data$log.perc.sugar ~ binary.label, pch = 19, cex.axis = 1.4, cex.lab = 1.5,
yaxt='n', ylim = c(1.2, 4.45))
segments(1, 4.3, 1, 4.35, lwd = 3)
segments(2, 4.3, 2, 4.35, lwd = 3)
segments(1, 4.35, 2, 4.35, lwd = 3)

text(1.5, 4.45, "pgls: p = 0.026", cex = 1.5)
text("B", x = 0.47, y = 1.2, cex = 2)
dev.off()
